        "path": "/books/kamil-al-ziyarat:2:92:3",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/24/2/92/3",
        "text": [
          " حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو الْيَسَعِ قَالَ سَأَلَ رَجُلٌ أَبَا عَبْدِ اللَّهِ (ع) وَ أَنَا أَسْمَعُ قَالَ آخُذُ مِنْ طِينِ قَبْرِ الْحُسَيْنِ يَكُونُ عِنْدِي أَطْلُبُ بَرَكَتَهُ قَالَ لَا بَأْسَ بِذَلِكَ"
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.sayyid-mohsen-al-husayni-al-milani": [
            "3. My father narrated to me from Sa’d ibn ‘Abdillāh, from Ayyūb ibn Nūḥ, from ‘Abdillāh ibn Mughīrah, from Abil Yasa’, who said: I heard a man ask Abā ‘Abdillāh (Imam Sādiq (a.s.)), “Can I take some of the clay of the grave of Ḥusain (a.s.) and keep it with me to seek blessings from it?” Imam (a.s.) replied, “There is nothing wrong with that.”"
          ]
        }
      },
